---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions"
  description="OutMore Adventures terms and conditions for booking and participating in our Yosemite experiences."
>
  <section class="py-20 sm:py-24 bg-valley-cream">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="mb-4">Terms & Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-granite-mid text-sm mb-12">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-granite-mid leading-relaxed">
        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Booking & Payment</h2>
          <p>
            All bookings are made through our booking partner, FlyBook. By making a reservation, you agree
            to the payment terms presented at the time of booking. Full payment is required to confirm your spot.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Cancellation Policy</h2>
          <p>
            Cancellations made 48 or more hours before your scheduled experience will receive a full refund.
            Cancellations made within 48 hours of the experience are non-refundable. No-shows are non-refundable.
            OutMore Adventures reserves the right to cancel or reschedule experiences due to weather or safety
            concerns, in which case a full refund or rescheduling will be offered.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Assumption of Risk</h2>
          <p>
            Participation in OutMore Adventures experiences involves inherent risks associated with outdoor
            activities in a national park setting. Participants acknowledge these risks and agree to follow
            all safety instructions provided by their guide. Participants are responsible for their own physical
            fitness and health.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Conduct</h2>
          <p>
            Participants are expected to follow all National Park Service regulations, respect the natural
            environment, and follow the instructions of their guide. OutMore Adventures reserves the right
            to remove any participant whose behavior threatens the safety or experience of the group.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Photography & Media</h2>
          <p>
            OutMore Adventures may take photographs or video during experiences for use on our website,
            social media, and marketing materials. If you prefer not to be photographed, please inform
            your guide at the beginning of the experience.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            OutMore Adventures' liability is limited to the cost of the experience purchased. We are not
            liable for personal injury, property damage, or loss arising from participation in our experiences,
            except where caused by our gross negligence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Operating Authority</h2>
          <p>
            OutMore Adventures operates under permit from the National Park Service, Yosemite National Park.
            All experiences are conducted in compliance with NPS regulations and permit conditions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these terms? Contact us at
            <a href="mailto:hello@outmoreadventures.com" class="text-sequoia hover:underline">hello@outmoreadventures.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
